  "doc_id": "45577",
  "text": "Ultrathin and straight Au NWs Fig. 6A are prepared easily by adding an oil-soluble reducing agent into C18AA toluene organogels containing HAuCl 4 . The lamellar structure of C18AA is vital for the formation of Au NWs, because the reduction of HAuCl 4 in C18AA solutions instead of in the gels results in the formation of Au nanoparticles NPs only without the formation of Au NWs. Further, high-resolution TEM images revealed that ultrathin Au NWs grow in the 111 direction, because a periodic fringe corresponding to the 111 lattice spacing is observed along the long axis of the Au NWs Fig. 6B . This result indicates that the side face of Au NWs has a large amount of 100 and/or 110 crystal facets. This result is consistent with the fact that C18AA molecules adsorb on the 100 and 110 crystal facets and hardly adsorb on the 111 crystal facet [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
